snippets.snippet: Got in to Seville well after most places were closed for the evening except for the bars. Too tired for those we chose to try a Spanish version of the Whopper. Honestly, not bad. Yeah, I know, going all the way to Spain and eat in an American burger bar is pretty lame, but it filled the need.

snippets.snippet: Ok, it's Burger King in Spain, where Americans can enjoy the novelty of ordering beer with their Whopper. This place has a huge seating area inside with A/C which is great on a hot summer day. However, if you're only visiting Seville for a couple of days, go get some authentic tapas instead of a hamburger that you can have back home.
